column5:
The Building Safety Regulator, under One HSE, will lead the regulatory regime to protect people and places in all forms of buildings. The Building Safety Regulator will have three key functions: 
a) leading the implementation of the new, more stringent regulatory regime for higher risk residential buildings in scope; 
b) promoting competence among industry professionals and regulators who have key roles in delivering safe, high-performing buildings; 
c) oversight of the building safety and performance system.
